text: Karlstad Cathedral () is a cathedral in the town of Karlstad in Sweden. Belonging to Karlstad Cathedral Parish of the Church of Sweden, it serves the Diocese of Karlstad, and was opened on 2 July 1730 (2 July 1730 according to the Old Style). == References == ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden cathedrals Category:Karlstad Category:18th-century buildings and structures
title: Karlstad Cathedral
